tldr: The user requested a review of a sleep questionnaire application against
  its acceptance criteria and a plan to implement missing features. The agent
  successfully implemented several high-priority features, including a tiredness
  severity scale with safety warnings, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep
  syndrome detection, and placeholder outbound resource links.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent performed an initial assessment, identifying several critical gaps in
  the existing implementation. Following this, the agent proceeded to implement
  key missing features. This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores, and integrating
  detection and recommendations for complex sleep disorders like COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. Furthermore, the agent enhanced the report
  generation by incorporating a dedicated section for external resources and
  began implementing weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness. The
  process involved meticulous updates across various code components, ensuring
  the application aligns more closely with the specified acceptance criteria.
